{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"As the demand for content for iPad increases, so does the need for tools to create that content. Mac OS X offers well-integrated automation technologies and tools, including Automator, Services, and AppleScript, that are ideal for generating content. Geared towards professional and non-professionals alike, this session will include hands-on tutorials covering how to use the automation technologies of Mac OS X to create and distribute HTML-based content for iPad."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2010\/302\/","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10-302-Automating-the-Creation-of-iPad-Content","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc10-302-automating-the-creation-of-ipad-content"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC10","title":"Automating the Creation of iPad Content","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC10"]]},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC10":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"WWDC